    {
      "id": "e3901aed3edfb2aa745269ae2c743995030ed731",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 109,
        "name": "Christopher J. Morrone",
        "email": "morrone2@llnl.gov",
        "username": "morrone"
      },
      "date": "2015-06-05 23:45:15.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 5: Code-Review-1\n\nThis patch kind of demonstrates that you are moving the \"cross compile\" capability away from being a generic cross compile capability and solidly into being crazy-phi environment specific.\n\nI think if you need crazy differences for Phi, you should really be creating a separate Phi-specific spec file.  The generic spec file is becoming far too complicated and difficult to maintain with all of these endless exceptions.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 5
    },
